From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0013/N] buildjdk-spec.gmk.in: also override EXTRA_ASFLAGS for buildjdk

`buildjdk-spec.gmk.in` (the template used by cross-compiles to neuter
TARGET-specific flags when compiling the BUILD-side JDK) already
overrides `EXTRA_CFLAGS`, `EXTRA_CXXFLAGS`, and `EXTRA_LDFLAGS` to
empty. It does NOT override `EXTRA_ASFLAGS`.

For us this matters because `--with-extra-asflags='-mabi=purecap
-march=morello'` propagates into the buildjdk's libjvm assembler
invocation (e.g. for `src/hotspot/os_cpu/linux_x86/linux_x86_64.S`),
and host clang-14 errors out with `unknown target CPU 'morello'`.

Same shape of fix as the existing three overrides; one line addition.

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md §6 (patch 0013)

--- a/make/autoconf/buildjdk-spec.gmk.in
+++ b/make/autoconf/buildjdk-spec.gmk.in
@@ -103,3 +103,4 @@
 override EXTRA_CFLAGS :=
 override EXTRA_CXXFLAGS :=
 override EXTRA_LDFLAGS :=
+override EXTRA_ASFLAGS :=
